Ecuador Says It Backs Using Local Currencies in Trade

-- B y   E l i a n a   R a s z e w s k i
-- 
2011-08-12T13:49:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-12/ecuador-says-it-backs-using-local-currencies-in-trade-correct-.html
(Corrects first sentence to say Borja criticized use of
dollar, not local currencies, in regional trade.)  Ecuador central bank President  Diego
Borja  said it “makes no sense” for South American countries to
use the  U.S. dollar  over local currencies for regional trade.  Borja spoke to reporters ahead of talks of the 12-member
Unasur political bloc in  Buenos Aires .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eliana Raszewski in Buenos Aires at 
 eraszewski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net  